searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Hibana","doc":"Hibana - A lightweight web framework for Elixir.","ref":"Hibana.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Overview - Hibana","doc":"Hibana is a lightweight web framework inspired by Plug and Phoenix,\ndesigned for simplicity and OTP integration.","ref":"Hibana.html#module-overview"},{"type":"module","title":"Core Components - Hibana","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.html#module-core-components"},{"type":"module","title":"Router - Hibana","doc":"Define routes using a DSL:\n\n    defmodule MyApp.Router do\n      use Hibana.Router.DSL\n\n      plug(Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser)\n      plug(Hibana.Plugins.Logger)\n\n      get \"/hello\", fn conn ->\n        json(conn, %{message: \"Hello, World!\"})\n      end\n\n      get \"/users\", UserController, :index\n      post \"/users\", UserController, :create\n    end","ref":"Hibana.html#module-router"},{"type":"module","title":"Controller - Hibana","doc":"Handle requests with response helpers:\n\n    defmodule MyApp.UserController do\n      use Hibana.Controller\n\n      def index(conn) do\n        json(conn, %{users: []})\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.html#module-controller"},{"type":"module","title":"Endpoint - Hibana","doc":"Start the HTTP server:\n\n    defmodule MyApp.Endpoint do\n      use Hibana.Endpoint, otp_app: :my_app\n    end","ref":"Hibana.html#module-endpoint"},{"type":"module","title":"Plugins - Hibana","doc":"Extend functionality with plugins:\n\n    plug(Hibana.Plugins.JWT, secret: \"secret\")\n    plug(Hibana.Plugins.CORS)\n    plug(Hibana.Plugins.RateLimiter)","ref":"Hibana.html#module-plugins"},{"type":"module","title":"Quick Start - Hibana","doc":"# mix.exs\n    def application do\n      [mod: {MyApp, []}]\n    end\n\n    # lib/my_app.ex\n    defmodule MyApp do\n      use Application\n      def start(_type, _args) do\n        children = [MyApp.Endpoint]\n        Supervisor.start_link(children, strategy: :one_for_one)\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.html#module-quick-start"},{"type":"module","title":"Available Plugins - Hibana","doc":"- `Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser` - Parse JSON/form bodies\n- `Hibana.Plugins.Session` - Cookie sessions\n- `Hibana.Plugins.JWT` - JWT authentication\n- `Hibana.Plugins.Auth` - Basic auth\n- `Hibana.Plugins.CORS` - Cross-origin support\n- `Hibana.Plugins.RateLimiter` - Rate limiting\n- `Hibana.Plugins.Cache` - ETS caching\n- `Hibana.Plugins.Logger` - Request logging\n- `Hibana.Plugins.HealthCheck` - Health endpoints\n- `Hibana.Plugins.Metrics` - Prometheus metrics\n- And more...","ref":"Hibana.html#module-available-plugins"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.version/0","doc":"Returns the application version.","ref":"Hibana.html#version/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Application","doc":"Hibana application supervision tree.","ref":"Hibana.Application.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Supervision Structure - Hibana.Application","doc":"The application starts:\n\n- `Hibana.Plugin.Registry` - Registry for plugins\n- `Hibana.Plugin.Supervisor` - DynamicSupervisor for plugins\n- `Hibana.Endpoint` - HTTP endpoint","ref":"Hibana.Application.html#module-supervision-structure"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Application","doc":"Add to your Mix config:\n\n    def application do\n      [\n        extra_applications: [:logger],\n        mod: {Hibana.Application, []}\n      ]\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Application.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Children - Hibana.Application","doc":"| Child | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| Plugin.Registry | Registry | Plugin registration |\n| Plugin.Supervisor | DynamicSupervisor | Plugin supervision |\n| Endpoint | Worker | HTTP server |","ref":"Hibana.Application.html#module-children"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket","doc":"The LiveView socket that holds the state.","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.assign/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.html#assign/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.assign/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.html#assign/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.new/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.html#new/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.push_event/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.Socket.html#push_event/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults","doc":"Default plug for request processing.","ref":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - Hibana.Plug.Defaults","doc":"- Fetches query parameters\n- Assigns params to conn","ref":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults.html#module-features"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Plug.Defaults","doc":"Included automatically in Endpoint:\n\n    use Plug.Builder, plug: Hibana.Plug.Defaults","ref":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"What It Does - Hibana.Plug.Defaults","doc":"1. Calls `fetch_query_params/1` to parse query string\n2. Assigns `params` to conn for easy access","ref":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults.html#module-what-it-does"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults.call/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.call/2 .","ref":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.init/1 .","ref":"Hibana.Plug.Defaults.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter","doc":"High-performance compiled router that generates pattern-match function clauses at compile time.\n\nRoutes are compiled into BEAM pattern matching, giving O(1) dispatch performance\nregardless of the number of routes.","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.CompiledRouter","doc":"defmodule MyApp.Router do\n      use Hibana.CompiledRouter\n\n      plug Hibana.Plugins.Logger\n      plug Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser\n\n      get \"/\", PageController, :index\n      get \"/users\", UserController, :index\n      post \"/users\", UserController, :create\n      get \"/users/:id\", UserController, :show\n      put \"/users/:id\", UserController, :update\n      delete \"/users/:id\", UserController, :delete\n\n      get \"/hello\" do\n        json(conn, %{message: \"Hello!\"})\n      end\n    end\n\nRoutes are compiled into pattern-match clauses like:\n\n    def match(\"GET\", [\"users\", id]) -> {:ok, UserController, :show, %{\"id\" => id}}\n\nThis gives BEAM-native performance — the Erlang VM's pattern matching engine\nhandles dispatch with no list iteration or string comparison loops.","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#module-usage"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.delete/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#delete/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.delete/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#delete/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.get/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#get/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.get/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#get/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.head/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#head/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.head/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#head/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.options/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#options/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.options/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#options/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.patch/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#patch/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.patch/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#patch/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.plug/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#plug/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.post/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#post/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.post/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#post/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.put/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#put/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.put/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CompiledRouter.html#put/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Controller","doc":"Base controller module for handling HTTP responses.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Controller","doc":"defmodule MyApp.UserController do\n      use Hibana.Controller\n\n      def index(conn) do\n        json(conn, %{users: []})\n      end\n\n      def show(conn) do\n        id = conn.params[\"id\"]\n        json(conn, %{user: %{id: id, name: \"User\"}})\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Response Helpers - Hibana.Controller","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-response-helpers"},{"type":"module","title":"json/1 - Hibana.Controller","doc":"Sends a JSON response with `application/json` content type.\n\n    json(conn, %{message: \"Hello!\"})","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-json-1"},{"type":"module","title":"html/1 - Hibana.Controller","doc":"Sends an HTML response with `text/html` content type.\n\n    html(conn, \" Hello! \")","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-html-1"},{"type":"module","title":"text/1 - Hibana.Controller","doc":"Sends a plain text response with `text/plain` content type.\n\n    text(conn, \"Hello, World!\")","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-text-1"},{"type":"module","title":"redirect/1 - Hibana.Controller","doc":"Redirects to another URL.\n\n    redirect(conn, to: \"/users\")","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-redirect-1"},{"type":"module","title":"send_file/2 - Hibana.Controller","doc":"Sends a file as a download.\n\n    send_file(conn, \"/path/to/file.pdf\")","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-send_file-2"},{"type":"module","title":"Parameter Access - Hibana.Controller","doc":"- `conn.params` - Path parameters (e.g., `/users/:id`)\n- `conn.body_params` - Request body as a map\n- `conn.query_params` - Query string parameters\n- `conn.req_headers` - Request headers","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-parameter-access"},{"type":"module","title":"Session Helpers - Hibana.Controller","doc":"- `get_session(conn, key)` - Get session value\n- `put_session(conn, key, value)` - Set session value","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#module-session-helpers"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.fetch_body_params/2","doc":"Fetch and parse body parameters from the connection.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#fetch_body_params/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.fetch_query_params/2","doc":"Fetch and parse query parameters from the connection.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#fetch_query_params/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.get_body_params/1","doc":"Get the parsed body parameters from the connection.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#get_body_params/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.get_query_params/1","doc":"Get the query string parameters from the connection.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#get_query_params/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.get_session/2","doc":"Get a session value by key.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#get_session/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.get_status/1","doc":"Get the current HTTP status code from the connection.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#get_status/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.html/2","doc":"Send an HTML response.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#html/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.json/2","doc":"Send a JSON response with the given data.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#json/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.put_session/3","doc":"Store a value in the session under the given key.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#put_session/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.put_status/2","doc":"Set the HTTP status code on the connection.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#put_status/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.redirect/2","doc":"Redirect to the given URL with a 302 status.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#redirect/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.render/4","doc":"Render a template using the given view module and send as HTML.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#render/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.req_header/2","doc":"Get the first value of a request header by name (case-insensitive).","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#req_header/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.send_file/3","doc":"Send a file as a download response with optional filename and content type.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#send_file/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Controller.text/2","doc":"Send a plain text response.","ref":"Hibana.Controller.html#text/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Endpoint","doc":"HTTP endpoint module that starts the Cowboy HTTP server.","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Endpoint","doc":"defmodule MyApp.Endpoint do\n      use Hibana.Endpoint, otp_app: :my_app\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Hibana.Endpoint","doc":"Add to your config:\n\n    config :my_app, MyApp.Endpoint,\n      http: [ip: {0, 0, 0, 0}, port: 4000],\n      secret_key_base: \"your-secret-key-base-at-least-64-bytes-long\"","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"module","title":"Starting the Endpoint - Hibana.Endpoint","doc":"The endpoint is typically started as part of your application supervision tree:\n\n    defmodule MyApp do\n      use Application\n\n      def start(_type, _args) do\n        children = [MyApp.Endpoint]\n        Supervisor.start_link(children, strategy: :one_for_one)\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html#module-starting-the-endpoint"},{"type":"module","title":"Child Spec - Hibana.Endpoint","doc":"The endpoint implements the `child_spec/1` callback for use in supervision trees:\n\n    Supervisor.child_spec({MyApp.Endpoint, []})","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html#module-child-spec"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Endpoint.call/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.call/2 .","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Endpoint.child_spec/1","doc":"Return a child specification for use in a supervision tree.","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Endpoint.init/1","doc":"A plug that may be invoked during requests.","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Endpoint.start_link/3","doc":"Called when the endpoint is started.","ref":"Hibana.Endpoint.html#start_link/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Pipeline","doc":"Middleware pipeline DSL with route groups and per-group plugs.","ref":"Hibana.Pipeline.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Pipeline","doc":"defmodule MyApp.Router do\n      use Hibana.CompiledRouter\n      import Hibana.Pipeline\n\n      # Global plugs\n      plug Hibana.Plugins.Logger\n\n      # API routes with auth\n      pipeline :api do\n        plug Hibana.Plugins.JWT, secret: \"secret\"\n        plug Hibana.Plugins.RateLimiter\n      end\n\n      # Public routes\n      pipeline :public do\n        plug Hibana.Plugins.CORS\n      end\n\n      scope \"/api\", pipeline: :api do\n        get \"/users\", UserController, :index\n        post \"/users\", UserController, :create\n      end\n\n      scope \"/\", pipeline: :public do\n        get \"/health\", HealthController, :index\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Pipeline.html#module-usage"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Pipeline.pipeline/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Pipeline.html#pipeline/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Pipeline.scope/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Pipeline.html#scope/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Router","doc":"Router module for handling HTTP requests with pattern matching.","ref":"Hibana.Router.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Router","doc":"defmodule MyApp.Router do\n      use Hibana.Router.DSL\n\n      plug(Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser)\n      plug(Hibana.Plugins.Logger)\n\n      get(\"/users\", MyApp.UserController, :index)\n      post(\"/users\", MyApp.UserController, :create)\n      get(\"/users/:id\", MyApp.UserController, :show)\n      put(\"/users/:id\", MyApp.UserController, :update)\n      delete(\"/users/:id\", MyApp.UserController, :delete)\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Router.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Route Matching - Hibana.Router","doc":"Routes are matched using pattern matching on the path:\n\n- Static paths: `/users`\n- Parameter paths: `/users/:id`\n- Wildcard paths: `/files/*path`","ref":"Hibana.Router.html#module-route-matching"},{"type":"module","title":"DSL Macros - Hibana.Router","doc":"The `Hibana.Router.DSL` module provides:\n\n- `get/3` - GET requests\n- `post/3` - POST requests\n- `put/3` - PUT requests\n- `delete/3` - DELETE requests\n- `patch/3` - PATCH requests\n- `options/3` - OPTIONS requests\n- `head/3` - HEAD requests\n\n- `plug/1` - Add a plug to the pipeline","ref":"Hibana.Router.html#module-dsl-macros"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Router.call/2","doc":"Process a request through the plug pipeline and match it against registered routes.","ref":"Hibana.Router.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Router.init/1","doc":"Initialize the router with routes and plugs from the given options.","ref":"Hibana.Router.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"DSL macros for defining routes in a router.","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html"},{"type":"module","title":"HTTP Method Macros - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-http-method-macros"},{"type":"module","title":"get/3 - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"Defines a GET route.\n\n    get \"/users\", UserController, :index\n    get \"/users/:id\", UserController, :show","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-get-3"},{"type":"module","title":"post/3 - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"Defines a POST route.\n\n    post \"/users\", UserController, :create","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-post-3"},{"type":"module","title":"put/3 - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"Defines a PUT route.\n\n    put \"/users/:id\", UserController, :update","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-put-3"},{"type":"module","title":"delete/3 - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"Defines a DELETE route.\n\n    delete \"/users/:id\", UserController, :delete","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-delete-3"},{"type":"module","title":"patch/3 - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"Defines a PATCH route.\n\n    patch \"/users/:id\", UserController, :partial_update","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-patch-3"},{"type":"module","title":"options/3 - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"Defines an OPTIONS route.\n\n    options \"/api/users\", MyController, :options","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-options-3"},{"type":"module","title":"head/3 - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"Defines a HEAD route.\n\n    head \"/users\", MyController, :head","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-head-3"},{"type":"module","title":"Inline Handlers - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"You can also define inline handlers using a block:\n\n    get \"/hello\" do\n      json(conn, %{message: \"Hello!\"})\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-inline-handlers"},{"type":"module","title":"Plug Pipeline - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"Add plugs to the pipeline:\n\n    plug(Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser)\n    plug(Hibana.Plugins.Logger)\n    plug(Hibana.Plugins.Session)","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-plug-pipeline"},{"type":"module","title":"Complete Example - Hibana.Router.DSL","doc":"defmodule MyApp.Router do\n      use Hibana.Router.DSL\n\n      plug(Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser)\n      plug(Hibana.Plugins.Logger)\n\n      get \"/\", PageController, :index\n      get \"/users\", UserController, :index\n      post \"/users\", UserController, :create\n      get \"/users/:id\", UserController, :show\n      put \"/users/:id\", UserController, :update\n      delete \"/users/:id\", UserController, :delete\n\n      get \"/hello\" do\n        json(conn, %{message: \"Hello!\"})\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#module-complete-example"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.delete/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#delete/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.delete/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#delete/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.get/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#get/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.get/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#get/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.head/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#head/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.head/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#head/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.options/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#options/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.options/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#options/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.patch/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#patch/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.patch/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#patch/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.plug/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#plug/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.post/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#post/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.post/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#post/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.put/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#put/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Router.DSL.put/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Router.DSL.html#put/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers","doc":"Test helpers for Hibana applications. Provides convenient functions\nfor testing controllers, routes, and plugs.","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.TestHelpers","doc":"defmodule MyApp.UserControllerTest do\n      use ExUnit.Case\n      use Hibana.TestHelpers\n\n      test \"index returns users\" do\n        conn = get(\"/users\")\n        assert json_response(conn, 200) == %{\"users\" => []}\n      end\n\n      test \"create user\" do\n        conn = post(\"/users\", %{name: \"Alice\", email: \"alice@test.com\"})\n        assert json_response(conn, 201)[\"name\"] == \"Alice\"\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#module-usage"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.assert_redirect/2","doc":"Assert redirect","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#assert_redirect/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.build_conn/4","doc":"Build a test connection","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#build_conn/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.delete/3","doc":"Make a DELETE request","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.get/3","doc":"Make a GET request","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html_response/2","doc":"Assert and return HTML response","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#html_response/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.json_response/2","doc":"Assert and decode JSON response","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#json_response/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.patch/3","doc":"Make a PATCH request","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#patch/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.post/3","doc":"Make a POST request","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#post/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.put/3","doc":"Make a PUT request","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#put/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.text_response/2","doc":"Assert and return text response","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#text_response/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.with_auth/2","doc":"Add authorization header","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#with_auth/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.TestHelpers.with_basic_auth/3","doc":"Add basic auth header","ref":"Hibana.TestHelpers.html#with_basic_auth/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Validator","doc":"Schema-based request parameter validation.","ref":"Hibana.Validator.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Validator","doc":"defmodule MyApp.UserParams do\n      use Hibana.Validator\n\n      validate do\n        field :name, :string, required: true, min: 2, max: 100\n        field :email, :string, required: true, format: ~r/@/\n        field :age, :integer, min: 0, max: 150\n        field :role, :string, one_of: [\"admin\", \"user\", \"mod\"]\n        field :tags, {:array, :string}, default: []\n      end\n    end\n\n    # In controller\n    def create(conn) do\n      case MyApp.UserParams.validate(conn.body_params) do\n        {:ok, params} -> json(conn, %{user: create_user(params)})\n        {:error, errors} -> conn |> put_status(422) |> json(%{errors: errors})\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Validator.html#module-usage"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Validator.do_validate/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Validator.html#do_validate/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Validator.field/3","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Validator.html#field/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Validator.validate/1","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Validator.html#validate/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Cluster","doc":"Built-in cluster support with node discovery, distributed PubSub, and process distribution.","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Cluster","doc":"# In your application supervisor\n    children = [\n      {Hibana.Cluster, strategy: :gossip, port: 45892},\n      # or\n      {Hibana.Cluster, strategy: :epmd, hosts: [:\"app@node1\", :\"app@node2\"]},\n      # or\n      {Hibana.Cluster, strategy: :dns, query: \"app.local\"}\n    ]","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Distributed PubSub - Hibana.Cluster","doc":"# Subscribe to a topic\n    Hibana.Cluster.subscribe(\"events\")\n\n    # Publish to all nodes\n    Hibana.Cluster.broadcast(\"events\", {:new_event, data})\n\n    # Receive in subscribed processes\n    receive do\n      {:cluster_event, \"events\", {:new_event, data}} -> handle(data)\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#module-distributed-pubsub"},{"type":"module","title":"Node Discovery Strategies - Hibana.Cluster","doc":"- `:epmd` — Connect to known hosts via Erlang distribution\n- `:dns` — Discover nodes via DNS SRV/A records\n- `:gossip` — UDP gossip protocol for automatic discovery","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#module-node-discovery-strategies"},{"type":"module","title":"Cluster Info - Hibana.Cluster","doc":"Hibana.Cluster.nodes()        # All connected nodes\n    Hibana.Cluster.node_count()    # Number of nodes\n    Hibana.Cluster.healthy?()      # Cluster health check","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#module-cluster-info"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.broadcast/2","doc":"Broadcast a message to all subscribers on all nodes","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#broadcast/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.call_on/5","doc":"Call a function on a specific node","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#call_on/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.cast_on/4","doc":"Cast a function on a specific node (async)","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#cast_on/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.child_spec/1","doc":"Return a child specification for use in a supervision tree.","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.healthy?/0","doc":"Check if cluster is healthy","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#healthy?/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  GenServer.init/1 .","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.local_broadcast/2","doc":"Broadcast only to local node subscribers","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#local_broadcast/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.multicall/4","doc":"Call a function on all nodes and collect results","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#multicall/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.node_count/0","doc":"Number of connected nodes","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#node_count/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.nodes/0","doc":"Get all connected nodes","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#nodes/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.start_link/1","doc":"Start the cluster manager with the given discovery strategy and options.","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.subscribe/1","doc":"Subscribe current process to a topic","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#subscribe/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cluster.unsubscribe/1","doc":"Unsubscribe current process from a topic","ref":"Hibana.Cluster.html#unsubscribe/1"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Hibana.LiveView","doc":"LiveView behavior for real-time server-rendered HTML.","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Usage - Hibana.LiveView","doc":"# Define a LiveView\n    defmodule MyApp.CounterLive do\n      use Hibana.LiveView\n\n      def mount(_params, _session, socket) do\n        {:ok, assign(socket, count: 0)}\n      end\n\n      # Return HTML string\n      def render(assigns) do\n        \"  Count: #{assigns[:count]}  \"\n      end\n\n      def handle_event(\"increment\", _params, socket) do\n        {:noreply, assign(socket, count: socket.assigns.count + 1)}\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#module-usage"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.LiveView.handle_connect/1","doc":"Handle websocket connection","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#c:handle_connect/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.LiveView.handle_event/3","doc":"Handle incoming events from client (phx-click, phx-submit, etc.)","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#c:handle_event/3"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.LiveView.handle_info/2","doc":"Handle incoming info messages (from GenServer, etc.)","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#c:handle_info/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.LiveView.mount/3","doc":"Called when LiveView is mounted. Return {:ok, socket} or {:error, reason}.","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#c:mount/3"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.LiveView.render/1","doc":"Renders the LiveView template. Must return HTML string.","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#c:render/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.LiveView.terminate/2","doc":"Called when LiveView is being terminated","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#c:terminate/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.connected/1","doc":"Marks socket as connected (after WebSocket handshake).","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#connected/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.push/3","doc":"Pushes an event to the client.","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#push/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.redirect/2","doc":"Redirects to a different URL.","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#redirect/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.render_template/1","doc":"Renders a template with assigns.","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#render_template/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.LiveView.socket/3","doc":"Creates a new LiveView socket.","ref":"Hibana.LiveView.html#socket/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.SSE","doc":"Server-Sent Events (SSE) support for real-time streaming.","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.SSE","doc":"# In your controller\n    def stream(conn) do\n      conn = Hibana.SSE.init(conn)\n\n      # Send events\n      Hibana.SSE.send_event(conn, \"message\", %{text: \"Hello!\"})\n      Hibana.SSE.send_event(conn, \"update\", %{count: 42})\n\n      # Or stream from a GenServer/process\n      Hibana.SSE.stream(conn, fn send_fn ->\n        # send_fn sends an SSE event\n        send_fn.(\"heartbeat\", %{time: DateTime.utc_now()})\n        Process.sleep(1000)\n        send_fn.(\"heartbeat\", %{time: DateTime.utc_now()})\n      end)\n    end","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"With a topic (PubSub-style) - Hibana.SSE","doc":"def live_updates(conn) do\n      Hibana.SSE.subscribe(conn, \"updates\", fn event ->\n        # Transform events before sending\n        %{type: \"update\", data: event}\n      end)\n    end","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#module-with-a-topic-pubsub-style"},{"type":"module","title":"Event Format - Hibana.SSE","doc":"SSE events follow the W3C specification:\n\n    event: message\n    data: {\"text\":\"Hello!\"}\n    id: 1","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#module-event-format"},{"type":"module","title":"Options - Hibana.SSE","doc":"- `:keep_alive` - Send comment every N ms to keep connection alive (default: 15_000)\n- `:retry` - Client retry interval in ms (default: 3_000)","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#module-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.SSE.init/2","doc":"Initialize an SSE connection with proper headers.","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#init/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.SSE.send_comment/2","doc":"Send a comment (keep-alive).","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#send_comment/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.SSE.send_data/2","doc":"Send a data-only event (no event type).","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#send_data/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.SSE.send_event/4","doc":"Send an SSE event with optional event type and id.","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#send_event/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.SSE.stream/3","doc":"Stream events using a callback function.\nThe callback receives a send function that can be called to emit events.","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#stream/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.SSE.stream_loop/2","doc":"Stream events from a process mailbox. Listens for messages and sends them as SSE events.\n\nExpects messages in the format `{:sse_event, type, data}`.\nStops when receiving `:sse_close` or when the connection is closed.","ref":"Hibana.SSE.html#stream_loop/2"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Hibana.WebSocket","doc":"WebSocket handler behavior for Hibana.","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Usage - Hibana.WebSocket","doc":"defmodule MyApp.ChatSocket do\n      use Hibana.WebSocket\n\n      def handle_in(msg, state) do\n        {:reply, {:text, \"echo: #{msg}\"}, state}\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#module-usage"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Routing - Hibana.WebSocket","doc":"In your router, call `Hibana.WebSocket.upgrade/3`:\n\n    get \"/ws/chat\", fn conn ->\n      Hibana.WebSocket.upgrade(conn, MyApp.ChatSocket)\n    end\n\nOr in a controller:\n\n    def websocket(conn) do\n      Hibana.WebSocket.upgrade(conn, MyApp.ChatSocket)\n    end","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#module-routing"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.handle_binary/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#c:handle_binary/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.handle_connect/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#c:handle_connect/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.handle_disconnect/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#c:handle_disconnect/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.handle_in/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#c:handle_in/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.handle_info/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#c:handle_info/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.init/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#c:init/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.start_link/2","doc":"Starts a WebSocket handler.","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#start_link/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.upgrade/3","doc":"Upgrades an HTTP connection to WebSocket.\n\nThis initiates the Cowboy WebSocket upgrade handshake. The `handler` module\nmust `use Hibana.WebSocket` and implement the required callbacks.","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.html#upgrade/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.WebSocket.CowboyAdapter","doc":"Bridges Hibana.WebSocket callbacks to Cowboy's cowboy_websocket behavior.\n\nThis module is used internally by `Hibana.WebSocket.upgrade/3`.\nUsers should not interact with it directly.","ref":"Hibana.WebSocket.CowboyAdapter.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker","doc":"Circuit breaker for external service calls. Prevents cascading failures\nby stopping calls to failing services.","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html"},{"type":"module","title":"States - Hibana.CircuitBreaker","doc":"- `:closed` - Normal operation, calls pass through\n- `:open` - Service is down, calls fail immediately\n- `:half_open` - Testing if service recovered","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html#module-states"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.CircuitBreaker","doc":"# Start a circuit breaker\n    Hibana.CircuitBreaker.start_link(\n      name: :payment_api,\n      threshold: 5,        # failures before opening\n      timeout: 30_000,     # ms before trying half-open\n      reset_timeout: 60_000 # ms before full reset\n    )\n\n    # Use it\n    case Hibana.CircuitBreaker.call(:payment_api, fn ->\n      HTTPClient.post(\"https://api.stripe.com/charge\", body)\n    end) do\n      {:ok, result} -> handle_success(result)\n      {:error, :circuit_open} -> handle_fallback()\n      {:error, reason} -> handle_error(reason)\n    end","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html#module-usage"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.call/2","doc":"Execute a function through the circuit breaker","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  GenServer.init/1 .","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.reset/1","doc":"Manually reset the circuit breaker","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html#reset/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.status/1","doc":"Get current state","ref":"Hibana.CircuitBreaker.html#status/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Cron","doc":"Built-in cron scheduler. Schedule recurring jobs with cron expressions.","ref":"Hibana.Cron.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Cron","doc":"defmodule MyApp.Scheduler do\n      use Hibana.Cron\n\n      schedule \"*/5 * * * *\", MyApp.CleanupJob        # Every 5 minutes\n      schedule \"0 * * * *\", MyApp.HourlyReport         # Every hour\n      schedule \"0 0 * * *\", MyApp.DailyDigest           # Daily at midnight\n      schedule \"0 0 * * 1\", MyApp.WeeklyReport          # Monday at midnight\n    end\n\n    # Add to supervision tree\n    children = [MyApp.Scheduler]","ref":"Hibana.Cron.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Cron Expression Format - Hibana.Cron","doc":"minute (0-59)\n    hour (0-23)\n    day of month (1-31)\n    month (1-12)\n    day of week (0-6, 0=Sunday)\n\n    * * * * *\n\nSupports: `*`, `*/N`, `N`, `N-M`, `N,M,O`","ref":"Hibana.Cron.html#module-cron-expression-format"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Cron.matches?/6","doc":"Check if a cron expression matches the given time components","ref":"Hibana.Cron.html#matches?/6"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Cron.schedule/2","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Cron.html#schedule/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Job","doc":"Background job queue module using OTP.","ref":"Hibana.Job.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Job","doc":"defmodule MyJob do\n      use Hibana.Job\n\n      def perform(data) do\n        IO.inspect(data, label: \"Processing job\")\n      end\n    end\n\n    # Enqueue a job\n    MyJob.enqueue(%{user_id: 123, action: \"send_email\"})","ref":"Hibana.Job.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue","doc":"High-performance persistent job queue with disk spillover and backpressure.\n\nSupports millions of jobs with automatic disk spillover when memory limits\nare reached. Uses DETS for persistence and ETS for hot jobs.","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.PersistentQueue","doc":"# Start the queue\n    {:ok, _pid} = Hibana.PersistentQueue.start_link(\n      name: :jobs,\n      max_memory_jobs: 10_000,\n      data_dir: \"priv/queue\",\n      concurrency: 10\n    )\n\n    # Enqueue a job\n    Hibana.PersistentQueue.enqueue(:jobs, MyWorker, %{user_id: 123})\n\n    # Enqueue with priority (lower = higher priority)\n    Hibana.PersistentQueue.enqueue(:jobs, MyWorker, %{data: \"urgent\"}, priority: 0)\n\n    # Enqueue with delay\n    Hibana.PersistentQueue.enqueue(:jobs, MyWorker, %{}, delay: 60_000)\n\n    # Get queue stats\n    Hibana.PersistentQueue.stats(:jobs)\n\n    # Pause/resume processing\n    Hibana.PersistentQueue.pause(:jobs)\n    Hibana.PersistentQueue.resume(:jobs)","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - Hibana.PersistentQueue","doc":"- **Disk spillover**: When memory jobs exceed `max_memory_jobs`, older jobs spill to DETS\n- **Backpressure**: Returns `{:error, :queue_full}` when disk queue exceeds limits\n- **Concurrency control**: Configurable number of concurrent workers\n- **Priority queues**: Jobs with lower priority numbers are processed first\n- **Retry with exponential backoff**: Failed jobs retry with increasing delays\n- **Persistence**: Jobs survive process restarts via DETS\n- **Graceful shutdown**: Waits for in-flight jobs before stopping","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#module-features"},{"type":"module","title":"Options - Hibana.PersistentQueue","doc":"- `:name` — Queue name (default: `__MODULE__`)\n- `:max_memory_jobs` — Max jobs in ETS before spilling to disk (default: 10_000)\n- `:max_disk_jobs` — Max jobs on disk (default: 1_000_000)\n- `:data_dir` — Directory for DETS files (default: `\"priv/queue\"`)\n- `:concurrency` — Max concurrent job workers (default: `System.schedulers_online()`)\n- `:poll_interval` — How often to check for new jobs in ms (default: 100)","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#module-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.child_spec/1","doc":"Return a child specification for use in a supervision tree.","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.clear/1","doc":"Clear all jobs from both memory and disk queues.","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#clear/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.enqueue/4","doc":"Enqueue a job with the given worker module, args, and options (priority, delay, max_retries).","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#enqueue/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  GenServer.init/1 .","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.pause/1","doc":"Pause job processing. Existing in-flight jobs will complete.","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#pause/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.resume/1","doc":"Resume job processing after a pause.","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#resume/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.start_link/1","doc":"Start the persistent queue process with the given options.","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.stats/1","doc":"Return queue statistics including memory jobs, disk jobs, and in-flight count.","ref":"Hibana.PersistentQueue.html#stats/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Queue","doc":"Persistent background job queue with GenServer and Erlang processes.","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Queue","doc":"# Define a job\n    defmodule SendEmailJob do\n      use Hibana.Queue.Job\n\n      def perform(data) do\n        IO.puts(\"Sending email to: #{data[:to]}\")\n      end\n    end\n\n    # Enqueue with delay (in milliseconds)\n    SendEmailJob.enqueue(%{to: \"user@example.com\"}, delay: 5000)\n\n    # Enqueue with retry\n    SendEmailJob.enqueue(%{to: \"user@example.com\"}, retry: 3)","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html#module-usage"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Queue.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Queue.clear/0","doc":"Clear all jobs from queue.","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html#clear/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Queue.enqueue/3","doc":"Enqueue a job to be processed.","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html#enqueue/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Queue.enqueue_at/4","doc":"Enqueue a job to be processed at a specific time.","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html#enqueue_at/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Queue.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  GenServer.init/1 .","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Queue.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Queue.stats/0","doc":"Get queue statistics.","ref":"Hibana.Queue.html#stats/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload","doc":"Large file upload support with chunked/resumable uploads (100GB+).\n\nSupports streaming multipart parsing without loading the entire file into memory,\nchunked uploads with resume capability, and progress tracking.","ref":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.ChunkedUpload","doc":"# Simple streaming upload (handles any size)\n    def upload(conn) do\n      {:ok, file_info} = Hibana.ChunkedUpload.receive(conn,\n        upload_dir: \"priv/uploads\",\n        max_size: :infinity\n      )\n      json(conn, file_info)\n    end\n\n    # Chunked/resumable upload\n    # Client sends chunks with headers:\n    #   X-Upload-Id: unique-id\n    #   X-Chunk-Number: 0\n    #   X-Total-Chunks: 100\n    #   Content-Range: bytes 0-1048575/104857600\n\n    def chunked_upload(conn) do\n      case Hibana.ChunkedUpload.receive_chunk(conn, upload_dir: \"priv/uploads\") do\n        {:ok, :complete, file_info} -> json(conn, %{status: \"complete\", file: file_info})\n        {:ok, :partial, progress} -> json(conn, %{status: \"uploading\", progress: progress})\n        {:error, reason} -> json(conn |> put_status(400), %{error: reason})\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - Hibana.ChunkedUpload","doc":"- **Streaming**: Never loads full file into memory, streams directly to disk\n- **Resumable**: Client can resume interrupted uploads\n- **Progress**: Track upload progress per chunk\n- **Integrity**: SHA256 checksum verification\n- **Cleanup**: Automatic cleanup of stale partial uploads","ref":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.html#module-features"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.cleanup_stale/2","doc":"Clean up stale partial uploads older than `max_age` seconds.","ref":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.html#cleanup_stale/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.receive/2","doc":"Receive a file upload by streaming the body directly to disk.\nNever loads the entire file into memory.","ref":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.html#receive/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.receive_chunk/2","doc":"Receive a chunk of a resumable upload.\nReturns `{:ok, :complete, file_info}` when all chunks received,\nor `{:ok, :partial, progress}` when more chunks expected.","ref":"Hibana.ChunkedUpload.html#receive_chunk/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.CodeReloader","doc":"Hot code reloading for development. Watches source files and automatically\nrecompiles when changes are detected.","ref":"Hibana.CodeReloader.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.CodeReloader","doc":"# Add to your supervision tree (dev only)\n    if Mix.env() == :dev do\n      children = [\n        {Hibana.CodeReloader, dirs: [\"lib\"], interval: 1_000}\n      ]\n    end","ref":"Hibana.CodeReloader.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Options - Hibana.CodeReloader","doc":"- `:dirs` - Directories to watch (default: `[\"lib\"]`)\n- `:interval` - Poll interval in ms (default: `1_000`)\n- `:callback` - Function called after recompile (default: `nil`)","ref":"Hibana.CodeReloader.html#module-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CodeReloader.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Hibana.CodeReloader.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CodeReloader.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  GenServer.init/1 .","ref":"Hibana.CodeReloader.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.CodeReloader.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.CodeReloader.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.EventStore","doc":"Event sourcing with GenServer, ETS storage, projections, and subscriptions.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.EventStore","doc":"{:ok, store} = Hibana.EventStore.start_link(name: :my_store)\n\n    Hibana.EventStore.append(store, \"user-1\", [\n      %{type: \"user_created\", data: %{name: \"Alice\"}},\n      %{type: \"user_updated\", data: %{name: \"Bob\"}}\n    ])\n\n    Hibana.EventStore.read(store, \"user-1\")\n\n    Hibana.EventStore.subscribe(store, \"user_*\")\n\n    Hibana.EventStore.register_projection(store, :user_count, fn\n      %{type: \"user_created\"}, state -> (state || 0) + 1\n      _, state -> state || 0\n    end)\n\n    Hibana.EventStore.projection(store, :user_count)","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#module-usage"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.all_events/1","doc":"Get all events in the store, ordered by sequence number.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#all_events/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.append/3","doc":"Append events to an aggregate stream.\nEvents are maps with at least a `:type` key.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#append/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.projection/2","doc":"Get the current state of a projection.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#projection/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.read/2","doc":"Read all events for an aggregate.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#read/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.register_projection/3","doc":"Register a projection with a reducer function.\nThe reducer receives `(event, current_state)` and returns new state.\nAutomatically replays all existing events.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#register_projection/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.start_link/1","doc":"Start the event store.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.subscribe/2","doc":"Subscribe to events matching a pattern.\nPattern supports wildcards with `*`.\nThe calling process will receive `{:event, event}` messages.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#subscribe/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.EventStore.unsubscribe/1","doc":"Unsubscribe from events.","ref":"Hibana.EventStore.html#unsubscribe/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Features","doc":"Feature toggle system for enabling/disabling plugins and modules via config.","ref":"Hibana.Features.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Features","doc":"In `config/config.exs`, list which features are enabled:\n\n    config :hibana, :features, [\n      Hibana.Plugins.Logger,\n      Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser,\n      Hibana.Plugins.CORS,\n      Hibana.Plugins.JWT,\n      # Hibana.Plugins.RateLimiter,    # <-- commented = disabled\n      # Hibana.Plugins.GraphQL,        # <-- commented = disabled\n    ]\n\nOr use a map for explicit on/off:\n\n    config :hibana, :features, %{\n      Hibana.Plugins.Logger => true,\n      Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser => true,\n      Hibana.Plugins.CORS => true,\n      Hibana.Plugins.RateLimiter => false,   # disabled\n      Hibana.Plugins.GraphQL => false,        # disabled\n    }","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"In your Router - Hibana.Features","doc":"defmodule MyApp.Router do\n      use Hibana.CompiledRouter\n      import Hibana.Features\n\n      # Only loads if enabled in config\n      feature_plug Hibana.Plugins.Logger\n      feature_plug Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser\n      feature_plug Hibana.Plugins.CORS, origins: [\"*\"]\n      feature_plug Hibana.Plugins.RateLimiter, max_requests: 100\n      feature_plug Hibana.Plugins.JWT, secret: \"secret\"\n\n      get \"/\", PageController, :index\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#module-in-your-router"},{"type":"module","title":"Runtime Check - Hibana.Features","doc":"if Hibana.Features.enabled?(Hibana.Plugins.RateLimiter) do\n      # rate limiter logic\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#module-runtime-check"},{"type":"module","title":"Supervisor Children - Hibana.Features","doc":"# Only start enabled services\n    children = Hibana.Features.filter_children([\n      {Hibana.Cluster, strategy: :epmd},\n      {Hibana.PersistentQueue, name: :jobs},\n      {Hibana.Plugins.Metrics, []},\n    ])","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#module-supervisor-children"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Features.disable/1","doc":"Disable a feature at runtime","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#disable/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Features.enable/1","doc":"Enable a feature at runtime","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#enable/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Features.enabled?/1","doc":"Check if a feature/module is enabled in config","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#enabled?/1"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Features.feature_plug/2","doc":"Conditionally add a plug only if the module is enabled in config","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#feature_plug/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Features.filter_children/1","doc":"Filter a list of supervisor children, keeping only enabled ones","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#filter_children/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Features.list_disabled/0","doc":"List all disabled features","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#list_disabled/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Features.list_enabled/0","doc":"List all enabled features","ref":"Hibana.Features.html#list_enabled/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.FileStreamer","doc":"Zero-copy file streaming using sendfile(2) syscall for maximum performance.\n\nUses the kernel's sendfile syscall to transfer files directly from disk to socket\nwithout copying through userspace, achieving maximum throughput.","ref":"Hibana.FileStreamer.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.FileStreamer","doc":"# Stream a file with zero-copy (fastest)\n    Hibana.FileStreamer.send_file(conn, \"/path/to/file.mp4\")\n\n    # Stream with range support (for video/audio seeking)\n    Hibana.FileStreamer.send_file(conn, \"/path/to/video.mp4\", range: true)\n\n    # Stream with custom content type\n    Hibana.FileStreamer.send_file(conn, \"/path/to/data.bin\",\n      content_type: \"application/octet-stream\",\n      filename: \"download.bin\"\n    )\n\n    # Chunked streaming from an Elixir Stream\n    Hibana.FileStreamer.stream_chunks(conn, File.stream!(\"/path/to/large.csv\", [], 64_000))","ref":"Hibana.FileStreamer.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - Hibana.FileStreamer","doc":"- Zero-copy via `Plug.Conn.send_file/5` (uses sendfile(2) under the hood)\n- HTTP Range request support for resumable downloads and seeking\n- Automatic MIME type detection\n- ETag and Last-Modified headers for caching\n- Chunked transfer encoding for dynamic streams","ref":"Hibana.FileStreamer.html#module-features"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.FileStreamer.send_file/3","doc":"Send a file using zero-copy sendfile(2).\nSupports range requests for resumable downloads and media seeking.","ref":"Hibana.FileStreamer.html#send_file/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.FileStreamer.stream_chunks/3","doc":"Stream chunks from an enumerable (e.g., File.stream!).\nUses chunked transfer encoding.","ref":"Hibana.FileStreamer.html#stream_chunks/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.GenServer","doc":"Base GenServer module for Hibana applications.","ref":"Hibana.GenServer.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - Hibana.GenServer","doc":"- Sensible defaults for common use cases\n- Automatic naming via `name: __MODULE__`\n- Standard init/1 callback pattern","ref":"Hibana.GenServer.html#module-features"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Hibana.GenServer","doc":"defmodule MyApp.StateManager do\n      use Hibana.GenServer\n\n      def start_link(opts) do\n        GenServer.start_link(__MODULE__, opts, name: __MODULE__)\n      end\n\n      def get_state, do: GenServer.call(__MODULE__, :get_state)\n      def update_state(new_state), do: GenServer.cast(__MODULE__, {:update_state, new_state})\n\n      def handle_call(:get_state, _from, state) do\n        {:reply, state, state}\n      end\n\n      def handle_cast({:update_state, new_state}, _state) do\n        {:noreply, new_state}\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.GenServer.html#module-example"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.GenServer","doc":"{:ok, pid} = MyApp.StateManager.start_link([])\n    GenServer.call(MyApp.StateManager, :get_state)","ref":"Hibana.GenServer.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.OTPCache","doc":"OTP-based in-memory cache using GenServer with TTL support.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - Hibana.OTPCache","doc":"- Key-value storage with automatic expiration\n- TTL (Time-To-Live) support in milliseconds\n- Eviction when max size is reached\n- Automatic cleanup of expired entries\n- `get_or_compute` for cache-aside pattern","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#module-features"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.OTPCache","doc":"# Start the cache\n    Hibana.OTPCache.start_link(name: :my_cache)\n\n    # Set a value with TTL (60 seconds)\n    Hibana.OTPCache.put(:my_cache, \"user:1\", user_data, ttl: 60_000)\n\n    # Get a value\n    Hibana.OTPCache.get(:my_cache, \"user:1\")\n\n    # Get or compute (lazy loading)\n    Hibana.OTPCache.get_or_compute(\n      :my_cache,\n      \"user:1\",\n      fn -> fetch_user_from_db(1) end,\n      ttl: 300_000\n    )\n\n    # Check if key exists\n    Hibana.OTPCache.exists?(:my_cache, \"user:1\")\n\n    # Delete a key\n    Hibana.OTPCache.delete(:my_cache, \"user:1\")\n\n    # Get cache statistics\n    Hibana.OTPCache.stats(:my_cache)\n\n    # Clear all entries\n    Hibana.OTPCache.clear(:my_cache)","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Options - Hibana.OTPCache","doc":"- `:name` - The server name (default: `__MODULE__`)\n- `:max_size` - Maximum number of entries (default: 1000)","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#module-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Supervision Integration - Hibana.OTPCache","doc":"children = [\n      {Hibana.OTPCache, name: :my_cache, max_size: 5000}\n    ]","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#module-supervision-integration"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.clear/1","doc":"Clear all cache entries.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#clear/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.delete/2","doc":"Delete a key from cache.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.exists?/2","doc":"Check if key exists and is not expired.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#exists?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.get/2","doc":"Get a value from cache.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.get_or_compute/4","doc":"Get a value or compute if not exists.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#get_or_compute/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  GenServer.init/1 .","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.keys/1","doc":"Get all keys.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#keys/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.put/4","doc":"Put a value into cache with optional TTL (in milliseconds).","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#put/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.OTPCache.stats/1","doc":"Get cache statistics.","ref":"Hibana.OTPCache.html#stats/1"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Hibana.Plugin","doc":"Behaviour for Hibana plugins.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Example - Hibana.Plugin","doc":"defmodule MyApp.AuthPlugin do\n      @behaviour Hibana.Plugin\n\n      def init(opts) do\n        # Initialize plugin with options\n        opts\n      end\n\n      def call(conn, _opts) do\n        # Process the request\n        conn\n      end\n\n      def before_send(conn, _opts) do\n        # Called before response is sent\n        conn\n      end\n    end","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.html#module-example"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.Plugin.before_send/2","doc":"Called just before the response is sent. Use this for cleanup or\nadding response headers.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.html#c:before_send/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.Plugin.call/2","doc":"Called for each request. This is the main entry point for the plugin.\nMust return the connection, possibly with modifications.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.html#c:call/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.Plugin.init/1","doc":"Called when the plugin is initialized. Use this to set up state and\nvalidate options.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.html#c:init/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Hibana.Plugin.start_link/1","doc":"Optional. Called when the plugin is started.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.html#c:start_link/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry","doc":"Registry for managing plugins at runtime.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - Hibana.Plugin.Registry","doc":"- Register/unregister plugins dynamically\n- List all registered plugins\n- Get plugin configuration\n- Thread-safe via GenServer","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#module-features"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Plugin.Registry","doc":"# Start the registry\n    {:ok, pid} = Hibana.Plugin.Registry.start_link(name: :my_plugins)\n\n    # Register a plugin\n    Hibana.Plugin.Registry.register(\n      :my_plugins,\n      :auth,\n      MyApp.AuthPlugin,\n      opts: [secret: \"secret\"]\n    )\n\n    # List all plugins\n    Hibana.Plugin.Registry.list_plugins(:my_plugins)\n\n    # Get a specific plugin\n    Hibana.Plugin.Registry.get_plugin(:my_plugins, :auth)\n\n    # Unregister a plugin\n    Hibana.Plugin.Registry.unregister(:my_plugins, :auth)","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Supervision Integration - Hibana.Plugin.Registry","doc":"children = [\n      {Hibana.Plugin.Registry, name: :plugin_registry}\n    ]","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#module-supervision-integration"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.get_plugin/2","doc":"Get a registered plugin's module and options by name.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#get_plugin/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  GenServer.init/1 .","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.list_plugins/1","doc":"List the names of all registered plugins.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#list_plugins/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.register/4","doc":"Register a plugin module under the given name with options.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#register/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.start_link/1","doc":"Start the plugin registry process.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.unregister/2","doc":"Unregister a plugin by name.","ref":"Hibana.Plugin.Registry.html#unregister/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Hibana.Warmup","doc":"Pre-load data on startup with a macro DSL.","ref":"Hibana.Warmup.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hibana.Warmup","doc":"defmodule MyApp.Warmup do\n      use Hibana.Warmup\n\n      warmup \"load config\" do\n        Application.fetch_env!(:my_app, :config)\n      end\n\n      warmup \"prime cache\" do\n        MyApp.Cache.prime()\n      end\n    end\n\nThen add to your supervision tree:\n\n    children = [\n      MyApp.Warmup\n    ]\n\nThe module runs all warmup tasks sequentially on `start_link/1` and\nreturns `:ignore` so it acts as a temporary worker.","ref":"Hibana.Warmup.html#module-usage"},{"type":"macro","title":"Hibana.Warmup.warmup/2","doc":"Define a warmup task with a name and body.","ref":"Hibana.Warmup.html#warmup/2"},{"type":"extras","title":"Overview","doc":"# Hibana 火花\n\n> *A single spark can start a prairie fire.*\n\nA lightweight Elixir web framework built on Plug and Cowboy for APIs and microservices. Direct routing like Sinatra, powerful plugins like Phoenix, full OTP under the hood.\n\n- **10 lines** to a production-grade API\n- **35 plugins** for auth, caching, real-time, monitoring\n- **Millions of connections** on the BEAM without changing a line\n- **Fault tolerance** -- Supervisors restart failures before users notice","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Quick Start - Overview","doc":"```elixir\n# lib/my_app/router.ex\ndefmodule MyApp.Router do\n  use Hibana.Router.DSL\n\n  plug Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser\n\n  get \"/hello\" do\n    json(conn, %{message: \"Hello, World!\"})\n  end\nend\n\n# lib/my_app/endpoint.ex\ndefmodule MyApp.Endpoint do\n  use Hibana.Endpoint, otp_app: :my_app\nend\n```\n\n```bash\nmix deps.get && mix run\ncurl http://localhost:4000/hello\n# => {\"message\":\"Hello, World!\"}\n```","ref":"readme.html#quick-start"},{"type":"extras","title":"Features - Overview","doc":"","ref":"readme.html#features"},{"type":"extras","title":"Core - Overview","doc":"| Module | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `Hibana.Router.DSL` | Sinatra-style routing with `get`, `post`, `put`, `patch`, `delete` |\n| `Hibana.CompiledRouter` | O(1) compiled pattern-match dispatch |\n| `Hibana.Controller` | Response helpers: `json`, `text`, `html`, `redirect`, `send_file` |\n| `Hibana.Endpoint` | Application entry point with Cowboy HTTP server |\n| `Hibana.Pipeline` | Middleware pipeline DSL |\n| `Hibana.Validator` | Request parameter validation with schemas |\n| `Hibana.TestHelpers` | Test utilities for request simulation |","ref":"readme.html#core"},{"type":"extras","title":"Real-time - Overview","doc":"| Module | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `Hibana.WebSocket` | WebSocket handler with `init`, `handle_in`, `handle_info` callbacks |\n| `Hibana.LiveView` | Server-rendered real-time HTML with event handling |\n| `Hibana.SSE` | Server-Sent Events with chunked transfer and keep-alive |\n| `Hibana.Cluster` | Distributed PubSub, node discovery, and RPC |","ref":"readme.html#real-time"},{"type":"extras","title":"Background Processing - Overview","doc":"| Module | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `Hibana.Queue` | Background job queue with retry and delayed execution |\n| `Hibana.Job` | Simple async job macro |\n| `Hibana.PersistentQueue` | Disk-backed queue with ETS/DETS spillover and backpressure |\n| `Hibana.Cron` | Cron-style scheduled tasks |\n| `Hibana.CircuitBreaker` | Circuit breaker for external service calls |","ref":"readme.html#background-processing"},{"type":"extras","title":"Infrastructure - Overview","doc":"| Module | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `Hibana.OTPCache` | GenServer-based in-memory cache with TTL |\n| `Hibana.GenServer` | Base GenServer with sensible defaults |\n| `Hibana.Plugin` | Plugin behavior and runtime registry |\n| `Hibana.FileStreamer` | Zero-copy file streaming with Range request support |\n| `Hibana.ChunkedUpload` | Streaming multipart uploads (100GB+) |\n| `Hibana.CodeReloader` | Hot code reloading for development |\n| `Hibana.EventStore` | Event sourcing support |\n| `Hibana.Warmup` | Application warmup routines |","ref":"readme.html#infrastructure"},{"type":"extras","title":"Plugins - Overview","doc":"**Security & Auth**\n`JWT` | `OAuth` (Google, GitHub, Facebook) | `Auth` | `APIKey` | `TOTP` | `RequestSigning` | `CORS` | `ScopedCORS` | `RateLimiter` | `DistributedRateLimiter`\n\n**Request Processing**\n`BodyParser` | `Session` | `RequestId` | `Compression` | `ContentNegotiation` | `APIVersioning` | `I18n`\n\n**Monitoring & Ops**\n`Logger` | `ColorLogger` | `Metrics` | `HealthCheck` | `GracefulShutdown` | `TelemetryDashboard` | `LiveDashboard`\n\n**Data & Content**\n`Cache` | `OTPCache` | `Static` | `Upload` | `GraphQL` | `Search` | `SEO`\n\n**Development & Admin**\n`ErrorHandler` | `DevErrorPage` | `Admin` | `LiveViewChannel`","ref":"readme.html#plugins"},{"type":"extras","title":"Showcases - Overview","doc":"","ref":"readme.html#showcases"},{"type":"extras","title":"REST API with Controller - Overview","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Router do\n  use Hibana.Router.DSL\n\n  plug Hibana.Plugins.BodyParser\n  plug Hibana.Plugins.CORS, origins: [\"*\"]\n\n  get \"/users\", UserController, :index\n  get \"/users/:id\", UserController, :show\n  post \"/users\", UserController, :create\nend\n\ndefmodule MyApp.UserController do\n  use Hibana.Controller\n\n  def index(conn), do: json(conn, %{users: [\"Alice\", \"Bob\"]})\n\n  def show(conn) do\n    json(conn, %{user: %{id: conn.params[\"id\"]}})\n  end\n\n  def create(conn) do\n    conn |> Plug.Conn.put_status(201) |> json(%{created: conn.body_params})\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#rest-api-with-controller"},{"type":"extras","title":"JWT-Protected API - Overview","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Router do\n  use Hibana.Router.DSL\n\n  plug Hibana.Plugins.JWT, secret: \"your-secret\", paths: [\"/api\"]\n\n  get \"/api/profile\" do\n    json(conn, %{user: conn.assigns[:current_user]})\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#jwt-protected-api"},{"type":"extras","title":"WebSocket Chat - Overview","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.ChatSocket do\n  use Hibana.WebSocket\n\n  def init(conn, _opts), do: {:ok, conn, %{}}\n\n  def handle_in(message, state) do\n    {:reply, {:text, \"Echo: #{message}\"}, state}\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#websocket-chat"},{"type":"extras","title":"Background Jobs with Retry - Overview","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.SendEmail do\n  use Hibana.Queue.Job\n\n  def perform(data) do\n    Mailer.send(data[:to], data[:subject], data[:body])\n  end\nend\n\n# Enqueue with 3 retries and 5-second delay\nSendEmail.enqueue(%{to: \"user@example.com\"}, delay: 5000, retry: 3)\n```","ref":"readme.html#background-jobs-with-retry"},{"type":"extras","title":"Cron Scheduler - Overview","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Scheduler do\n  use Hibana.Cron\n\n  cron \"*/5 * * * *\", :cleanup_sessions\n  cron \"0 0 * * *\", :daily_report\n\n  def cleanup_sessions, do: Session.cleanup_expired()\n  def daily_report, do: Reports.generate_daily()\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#cron-scheduler"},{"type":"extras","title":"Comparison - Overview","doc":"| | Hibana | Phoenix | Plug |\n|---|--------|---------|------|\n| **Setup** | Minimal | Generator with conventions | Minimal |\n| **Routing** | Sinatra-style DSL | MVC-style | Manual |\n| **Inline handlers** | Yes | No | No |\n| **Plugins** | 35 built-in | Rich ecosystem | Minimal |\n| **LiveView** | Basic pattern | Industry-leading | No |\n| **Learning curve** | ~1 hour | ~1 day | ~1 hour |\n| **Best for** | APIs, microservices | Full-stack web apps | Libraries, middleware |\n\nHibana is not a Phoenix replacement. Phoenix is the right choice for full-stack web applications with complex front-ends. Hibana targets developers building APIs, microservices, and lightweight backends who want direct routing with batteries included.","ref":"readme.html#comparison"},{"type":"extras","title":"The Name - Overview","doc":"> **火花** (Hibana) -- *noun.* A spark. The flash of light when steel strikes stone.\n\nIn the Japanese blacksmith tradition, the spark is the beginning of everything. Days of folding and hammering follow, but nothing starts without that initial flash from steel against stone. Hibana follows the same philosophy:\n\n1. **一撃 (Ichigeki)** -- One strike. One route. Start small.\n2. **重ねる (Kasaneru)** -- Layer by layer. Add plugins as you grow.\n3. **鍛える (Kitaeru)** -- Forge under pressure. The BEAM handles the heat.\n4. **折れない (Orenai)** -- Unbreakable. Supervisors catch every fall.","ref":"readme.html#the-name"},{"type":"extras","title":"Sample Apps - Overview","doc":"| App | Port | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `hello_world` | 4000 | Basic routing |\n| `rest_api` | 4001 | REST API with Users and Posts |\n| `auth_jwt` | 4002 | JWT authentication |\n| `websocket_chat` | 4003 | WebSocket chat |\n| `liveview_counter` | 4004 | LiveView counter |\n| `background_jobs` | 4005 | Background jobs with Queue |\n| `commerce` | 4010 | E-commerce API (products, cart, orders, JWT) |\n| `chess` | 4011 | Chess game server with WebSocket |\n| `tictactoe` | 4012 | Tic-Tac-Toe with AI (minimax) and WebSocket |\n| `telegram_bot` | 4013 | Telegram bot with webhook |\n\n```bash\ncd sample_apps/hello_world && mix deps.get && mix run\n```","ref":"readme.html#sample-apps"},{"type":"extras","title":"Commands - Overview","doc":"```bash\n# Server\nmix run                              # Start server\nmix server                           # Start server (alias)\n\n# Generators\nmix gen.app my_app                   # New project\nmix gen.controller User              # Controller\nmix gen.model User name:string       # Model\nmix gen.scaffold User name:string    # Full scaffold\nmix gen.migration create_users       # Migration\n\n# Utilities\nmix routes                           # List routes\nmix secret                           # Generate secret key\n\n# Database\nmix db.create                        # Create database\nmix db.migrate                       # Run migrations\nmix db.rollback                      # Rollback migration\nmix db.seed                          # Seed data\n\n# Tests\ncd apps/hibana && MIX_ENV=test mix test\ncd apps/hibana_plugins && MIX_ENV=test mix test\n```","ref":"readme.html#commands"},{"type":"extras","title":"Architecture - Overview","doc":"```\nhibana/\n├── apps/\n│   ├── hibana/                # Core framework\n│   ├── hibana_plugins/        # 35 built-in plugins\n│   ├── hibana_ecto/           # Database support (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB)\n│   └── hibana_generator/      # Mix tasks and project generator\n├── sample_apps/               # Demo applications\n└── config/\n```","ref":"readme.html#architecture"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - Overview","doc":"MIT -- see [LICENSE](LICENSE) for details.","ref":"readme.html#license"},{"type":"extras","title":"Changelog","doc":"# Changelog\n\nAll notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.\n\nThe format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/).\n\n## [0.1.0] - 2026-03-23","ref":"changelog.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Added - Changelog","doc":"- Core framework: Router DSL, Controller, Endpoint with Cowboy\n- Plugin system with behavior and runtime registry\n- 21 built-in plugins: CORS, RateLimiter, Auth, JWT, OAuth, Static, BodyParser, Session, Logger, ErrorHandler, GraphQL, Cache, OTPCache, HealthCheck, Metrics, APIVersioning, RequestId, ContentNegotiation, Upload, GracefulShutdown, LiveViewChannel\n- WebSocket handler with callbacks\n- LiveView server-rendered real-time HTML pattern\n- Background job queue with retry and delayed execution\n- GenServer base module with defaults\n- OTP cache with TTL support\n- Code reloader for development\n- Request validation\n- Circuit breaker\n- Cron scheduler\n- Cluster support with distributed PubSub\n- Admin dashboard plugin\n- Live dashboard plugin\n- Telemetry dashboard plugin\n- Project generator: `mix gen.app`\n- 6 sample applications","ref":"changelog.html#added"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}